[[File:IKEA-Museum-August-2016.jpg|thumb|The IKEA Museum in August 2016]] The '''IKEA Museum''' is a museum located in [[Älmhult]], Sweden, that opened to the public on June 30, 2016.<ref name="opened">{{cite web|title=Ikea museum opens in Sweden celebrating firm's history - BBC News|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-36671489|publisher=''[[BBC News]]''|accessdate=28 July 2016}}</ref> It presents the history of the Swedish furnishing company [[IKEA]].<ref name="IKEA Museum öppnar 30 juni i år">{{cite web|title=IKEA Museum öppnar 30 juni i år|url=http://www.allas.se/ikea-museum-oppnar-30-juni-i-ar/|website=Allas|accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> It replaced IKEA Through the Ages, a smaller 800 m<sup>2</sup> exhibition that showed 20 different room settings with IKEA furniture and objects.<ref name="Let Me Take You On a Tour of IKEA's Bizarre Corporate Museum">{{cite web|last1=Estes|first1=Adam Clark|title=Let Me Take You On a Tour of IKEA's Bizarre Corporate Museum|url=https://gizmodo.com/let-me-take-you-on-a-tour-of-ikeas-bizarre-corporate-mu-1707804814|website=Gizmodo|accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref name="There is an Ikea Museum at the Company’s Headquarters in Sweden">{{cite web|last1=Fessenden|first1=Marissa|title=There is an Ikea Museum at the Company’s Headquarters in Sweden|url=http://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/there-ikea-museum-companys-headquarters-sweden-180955503/?no-ist|website=Smithsonian Magazine|accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref>
The IKEA Museum is in the same building where the first IKEA store opened in 1958. The store moved to a new location in Älmhult in 2012. At this time, work began on converting the store into a museum, with an original planned opening date of 2015.<ref name="IKEA museum set for 2015 delivery">{{cite web|last1=Cha|first1=Frances|title=IKEA museum set for 2015 delivery|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2014/05/19/travel/ikea-museum/|website=CNN|accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref><ref name="IKEA plans to open museum">{{cite web|title=IKEA plans to open museum|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/destinations/europe/sweden/articles/IKEA-plans-to-open-museum/|website=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref> The facade of the building was restored to recreate its original appearance. The museum has an area of 3500 m<sup>2</sup>.<ref name="Älmhult – IKEA’s cradle">{{cite web|title=Älmhult – IKEA’s cradle|url=https://www.visitsmaland.se/en/article/701/almhult-och-markaryd/almhult-ikeas-cradle|website=Visit Småland|accessdate=20 April 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170122194648/https://www.visitsmaland.se/en/article/701/almhult-och-markaryd/almhult-ikeas-cradle#|archive-date=2017-01-22|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref name="IKEA will open museum at original location in Sweden">{{cite web|last1=Opam|first1=Kwame|title=IKEA will open museum at original location in Sweden|url=https://www.theverge.com/2014/5/12/5710304/ikea-will-open-museum-at-original-location-in-sweden|website=The Verge|accessdate=20 April 2016}}</ref>
